"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Several interactions are possible when a photon of light (excitation light) comes into contact with tissue. The photon may be reflected immediately, it may pass through the tissue for a certain distance to be absorbed by chromophores, or it can cause a light-tissue interaction resulting in a change in its wave-length, a phenomenon known as autofluorescence.",
